Eugen Ferdinand Pius Bernhard Felix Maria (Archduke Eugen) Habsburg-Lothringen aka von Österreich-Teschen

Born 21 May 1863 in Gross-Seelowitz, Mähren, Kaisertum Oesterreich

Ancestors

[spouse(s) unknown]

[children unknown]

Died 30 Dec 1954 at age 91 in Merano, Bolzano, Trentino-Alto Adige, Italia

Profile last modified 29 Oct 2022 | Created 13 Dec 2015

This page has been accessed 1,442 times.

Biography

Archduke Eugen Ferdinand Pius Bernhard Felix Maria of Austria-Teschen (21 May 1863 – 30 December 1954) was an Archduke of Austria and a Prince of Hungary and Bohemia. He was the last Grand Master of the Teutonic Knights from the Habsburg dynasty.

Eugen was the son of Karl Ferdinand, Archduke of Austria (son of Archduke Charles, Duke of Teschen) and of his wife Archduchess Elisabeth Franziska of Austria. He was born at the castle of Gross Seelowitz (Židlochovice), near Brünn (Brno) in Moravia. At his baptism he was given the names Eugen Ferdinand Pius Bernhard Felix Maria. His education was Spartan in character. His country living at Gross Seelowitz and holidays at Gmund alternated with a sound education and strict instruction.[1]
